    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-29T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-29T04:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/734: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 29, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1558. Department’s 1393, May 24.<note n="77" xml:id="d137fn77">Not printed; it
                        contained the information that the <hi rend="italic">President
                            Roosevelt</hi> had sailed May 24 and would arrive at Galway June 1
                        (340.1115A/693a).</note> This additional information was communicated to the
                    Foreign Office by note on May 25. The Foreign Office has now formally
                    acknowledged receipt of this note and has stated that it has not failed to
                    communicate the contents to the competent domestic authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
